  "title": "Logistic Operation Assistant (TUAS)**IMMEDIATE",
  "description": "<ul><li>Coordinating the receipt, storage, and distribution of goods and materials</li><li>Manage with the processing and tracking of orders and shipments</li><li>Collaborating with internal teams and external suppliers to resolve logistics-related issues</li><li>Providing administrative support to the logistics department, such as document preparation and data entry</li><li>Implementing and adhering to logistics policies, procedures and safety protocols</li><li>Contributing to the continuous improvement of logistics processes and systems</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum 1-2 years of experience in a logistics or supply chain role</li><li>Familiarity with inventory management systems and logistics software</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills to liaise with various stakeholders</li><li>Knowledge of logistics regulations, procedures and best practices</li><li>Proficient in MS Office</li><li><strong>Working location at Tuas</strong></li><li><strong>$2400 - $3000</strong></li><li><strong>Start work immediately</strong></li></ul>",
